description.narrative: Improved capacity of Ministry of Social Development and other government institutions to adopt and implement a national social protection plan with adequate budget, and to offer equitable social protection programmes for boys and girls, including adolescents, which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Child Protection â€“ Strengthen Families And Communities, Cross-Sectoral Adolescent Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Data And Child Protection, Early Childhood Development, Environmental Sustainability, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Public Finance And Local Governance, Social Exclusion â€“ Data And Evidence, Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Social Protection And Child Poverty. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Increased capacity of CONJUVE to promote adolescent participation, in particular of disadvantaged children, to develop their skills and opportunities to participate in decision making processes.

title.narrative: Improved capacity of Ministry of Social Development and other government institutions to adopt and implement a national socialprotection plan with adequate budget, and to offer equitable social protection programmes for boys and girls, including adolescents

description.narrative: UNICEF contributed to strengthening the national social protection system through provision of technical assistance to MIDES to implement a social household registry pilot project as well as updating of the Management Information System of the Bono Social cash transfer program.The Office provided technical assistance to MAGA to register agricultural producers affected by natural disaster for its social protetion scheme. UNICEF provided support to the updating of the National Policy on ECD. The Office also supported capacity-building among adolescents on social entrepreneurship though UPSHIFT and supported MINECO to integrate training activities on innovation and entrepreneurship in the Ministry portfolio. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2022
